summaries.short: Bob, Eureka, and Shangela work with a neurodivergent trans man, a struggling gay couple, and a cheerleader longing for approval.
summaries.full: In the Southern California town of Temecula, Bob, Eureka, and Shangela work with James, an often misgendered trans man navigating neurodiversity; Jake, his faith influencer mom Michelle, and his partner Brad; and Andrei, a cheerleader whose move back home finds him longing for his mother’s acceptance.

summaries.short: Pride Month is the perfect time for the queens to celebrate mayor Bruno Lozano’s inclusivity, Joey’s journey, and Esael’s coming out.​
summaries.full: Pride Month proves the perfect opportunity for Bob, Eureka, and Shangela to visit the border town of Del Rio, Texas. There, the queens celebrate gay identifying mayor Bruno Lozano’s positive impact on the community, Joey’s identity quest, and Esael’s coming out journey.

titles.full: Spartanburg, South Carolina

summaries.short: A year after meeting Noah, Faith, and Olin, the queens return to Spartanburg, SC to finish what they started.​
summaries.full: A year after their first visit was cut short due to the pandemic, Shangela, Bob, and Eureka return to Spartanburg, SC to catch up with Noah, who grapples with gender expression; plus-size lesbian model Faith; and Olin, who wants to bring his family together by walking in his brother’s shoes – literally.

titles.full: Selma, Alabama

summaries.short: In Selma, AL, Bob, Eureka, and Shangela use drag to spotlight Akeelah’s living out loud, release Joseph’s pain, and take care of Deborah.​
summaries.full: Bob, Eureka, and Shangela bring drag to Selma, AL, where the queer community remains hidden despite the city’s historical significance to the civil rights movement. There, they help recently transitioned Akeelah find the confidence to live life beyond closed doors, release Joseph’s deep-seated pain, and encourage Deborah to prioritize herself for a change.

summaries.short: Season One Finale. Bob, Eureka, and Shangela reflect on how drag changed their lives.
summaries.full: Season One Finale. When COVID-19 disrupts their production schedule, the queens do what they do best: they make it work. Featuring some never-before-seen performances, Bob, Eureka, and Shangela reflect – from the comfort of their homes – on how drag changed, and even saved, their lives.

summaries.short: The queens help a pastor promote allyship, inspire a refugee to celebrate himself, and facilitate a long overdue lesbian wedding.​
summaries.full: Hoping to open hearts and minds in Evansville, IN, Bob, Eureka, and Shangela help Methodist Pastor Craig promote LGBTQ equality to his congregants, inspire Tunisian refugee Kaïs to celebrate all facets of his entire identity, and facilitate the long-overdue wedding of civil rights activists Barbara and Yvon.

titles.short: Ruston, Louisiana
titles.full: Ruston, Louisiana

summaries.short: The queens storm Ruston, LA to shake things up for a young gay man determined to be himself; a straight ex-firefighter; and more
summaries.full: Bob, Eureka, and Shangela head south to Ruston, Louisiana to shake things up for a small town that's in need of some change. Among their drag children are: Jose, a young gay man tired of censoring himself in order to gain respect; and lifelong Ruston resident Stacy, an ex-firefighter & straight ally dedicated to using his influence to make LGBTQ community members feel welcome.
